04/05/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The defence ministry issued an order Thursday (1 May) forcing army staff to submit all available information on suspects wanted by the UN war crimes tribunal. 
The act applies to all professional armed and civilian personnel. 
Non-compliance will be considered a violation of military discipline and will result in serious sanctions, according to the ministry. 
The document includes procedures for apprehending and detaining war crimes suspects and is aimed at improving the country's co-operation with The Hague tribunal. 
(B92 - 02/05/03; Beta - 01/05/03)
